stylometry: Sensitivity analysis is important because it uses solvertable to find the best solution. It adds components like graphs and extra tables for the information - but it is unique because you must run solvertable with it - you can set how high, low, how long, the solvertable will run for to find the best solution. You will be able to see what it has found so far as it continues to search. You can then compare the answer with the same problem you did for say linear programming running with only Solver. It will either find the same solution or a better one. The goal is to find the best solution for a company or scenario.
